# CLAUDE.local.md (template)

Copy to `CLAUDE.local.md` and customize. This file is gitignored — your overrides will not be committed.

Use this for personal preferences and machine-specific notes Claude should respect during your sessions.

## My local WP install

- WP root: `/Users/me/Local Sites/wperp/app/public`
- Site URL: `http://wperp.local`
- DB: `wordpress`, prefix `wp_`
- Admin: `admin` / (in 1Password)

## My preferred workflow

- I run `npm run dev` in a separate terminal — do NOT start it for me.
- Use `composer phpcbf` before showing me a PHP diff.
- Skip running the acceptance suite — Selenium is not set up locally. Mention what tests I should run manually.
- Prefer Eloquent models over raw `$wpdb` in new code unless the surrounding file is raw.

## My branches / PR style

- Default base branch: `develop`
- I prefer short, imperative commit subjects (≤72 chars). Body explains *why*, not *what*.
- Open PRs in draft; I'll mark ready manually.

